This could all be coincidence... but given how sneaky...
body:
Taylor’s butterfly hints!

Okay, so Taylor’s been posting a lot of photos with butterfly themes:

This could all be coincidence… but given how sneaky Taylor is, I wouldn’t be surprised if it’s a theme for her next album!

If you look up butterfly symbolism, it brings up resurrection! Could this mean that the “old Taylor” is coming back from the dead?

Taylor Nation recently sent out promotional emails using the old logo, from the original album. Which, YOU GUESSED IT, has pictures of butterflies on it!

Again, this could all be completely coincidental. However when I reread Taylor’s 30 article, I saw this!

Could this be a hint that the curly haired old Taylor will be resurrected for her new album?

tags: it got me through my worst break up
summary:
sad beautiful tragic is extremely underrated 
it has some of her most meaningful and spot-on relatable heartbroken lyrics...
body:
sad beautiful tragic is extremely underrated

it has some of her most meaningful and spot-on relatable heartbroken lyrics

  • “words, how little they mean when you’re a little too late”
  • “good girls, hopeful they’ll be and long they will wait”
  • “time is taking its sweet time erasing you”

and don’t even get me STARTED on the bridge…

  • “distance, timing, breakdown, fighting, silence. this train runs off its tracks. kiss me, try to fix it. could you just try to listen? hang up. give up. for the life of us we can’t get back”

conclusion: sad beautiful tragic is an underrated heartbreak anthem that needs more appreciation

CASE 👏🏻 CLOSED 👏🏻
